title: Tahini Breakfast Cookies
date: 2023-08-23
category: breakfast
tags: oats, bar, granola
---

## Ingredients
* 6 cups rolled oats
* 1.5 cup almond flour
* 2 medium ripe banana
* 10 tbsp maple syrup
* 4 tbsp tahini (toasted, hulled ground sesame seeds)
* 3 tbsp ground flax seeds
* 3 tbsp chia seeds
* 1 tsp vanilla extract
* 0.67 cup walnuts or mixed nuts
* 1 cup cacao nibs/choc chips

## Instructions
1. Preheat oven to 325Â°F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
1. Blend the rolled oats in a blender for a few seconds leaving bits of larger oats.
1. Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
1. Roll 2 tablespoons of batter in a ball and place on the parchment paper.
1. Flatten all the cookies with your hand or a fork in 2 directions.
1. Bake for 12-15 minutes. Cool before eating.

[Source: Plant Based Cooking Diane Smith](https://www.plantbasedcooking.com/recipe/tahini-breakfast-cookies/)
